<br>
In HTML (the language used to write webpages) you can reference a local file on your personal hard drive by pointing to that file in the coding.  For example, clicking on <a href="file:///c:/windows/desktop">This Link</a> will take you to a new page showing you the contents of your desktop.<br>
<br>
How does it work?<br>
In referencing that link, I am pointing to the location: c:\windows\desktop.  So if you have a "C:\windows\desktop" the link will work for you.  If you don't, it won't.<br>
<br>
Why doesn't it work for everyone?<br>
Not all people use the default installation paths.  Some people may have separate or partitioned drives.  So the initial post was created assuming everyone installed Everquest into the "C:\program files\everquest" directory.  The second assumption is that you've taken screenshots.  If you have, then you'll most likely have the eq000001.bmp file.  Those people who don't have both of these will have the little "broken image X".<br>
<br>
Isn't that a security risk?<br>
Not really.  Any reference made in this manner is telling *your* computer to "look here".  The internet browser reads the information from the page, and spits it out.  If the location is foreign, it will go out and get it.  If it's local, it will pull it locally.<br>
<br>
So if the HTML told the brower to fetch:<br>
http://www.somebodysrl.com/images/image.gif<br>
The browser would go to that site to show the image.<br>
<br>
In this case, the HTML told the browser to fetch: <br>
file:///c:/program files/everquest/eq000001.bmp<br>
<br>
No information is sent from the local computer, to the remote computer.  (IE: The contents of your desktop are not being shared.  In addition, not everyone sees the same picture as you're seeing).<br>
<br>
This is a very elementary explanation, but hopefully it'll do the trick. <p><img src="http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/amalgam/forum/forumsig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A> at: 7/11/01 8:14:39 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3046.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3044.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.emailToFriend?topicID=3010.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.threadControl?topicID=3010.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3010.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3010.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgroveboardpostingrulesandpolicy">Board Posting Rules And Policy<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm22">Polls<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">G